#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.13"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.13:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.13:0.2"
msgid "2. Yamakavagga "
msgstr "2. Pairs "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 13. Paṭhamapubbesambodhasutta → sambodhasuttaṃ (bj) | sambodhena 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.13:0.3"
msgid "13. Paṭhamapubbesambodhasutta "
msgstr "13. Before My Awakening (Interior) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.7, sc1
msgctxt "sn35.13:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.13:1.2"
msgid "“Pubbeva me, bhikkhave, sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato etadahosi: "
msgstr "“Mendicants, before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on awakening—I thought: "

msgctxt "sn35.13:1.3"
msgid "‘ko nu kho cakkhussa assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇaṃ? "
msgstr "‘What’s the gratification, the drawback, and the escape when it comes to the eye … "

msgctxt "sn35.13:1.4"
msgid "Ko sotassa … pe … "
msgstr "ear … "

msgctxt "sn35.13:1.5"
msgid "ko ghānassa … "
msgstr "nose … "

msgctxt "sn35.13:1.6"
msgid "ko jivhāya … "
msgstr "tongue … "

msgctxt "sn35.13:1.7"
msgid "ko kāyassa … "
msgstr "body … "

msgctxt "sn35.13:1.8"
msgid "ko manassa assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇan’ti? "
msgstr "and mind?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.13:1.9"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me: "

msgctxt "sn35.13:1.10"
msgid "‘yaṃ kho cakkhuṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, ayaṃ cakkhussa assādo. "
msgstr "‘The pleasure and happiness that arise from the eye: this is its gratification. "

msgctxt "sn35.13:1.11"
msgid "Yaṃ cakkhuṃ aniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, ayaṃ cakkhussa ādīnavo. "
msgstr "That the eye is impermanent, suffering, and perishable: this is its drawback. "

msgctxt "sn35.13:1.12"
msgid "Yo cakkhusmiṃ chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ, idaṃ cakkhussa nissaraṇaṃ. "
msgstr "Removing and giving up desire and greed for the eye: this is its escape. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.13:1.13"
msgid "Yaṃ sotaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "The pleasure and happiness that arise from the ear … "

msgctxt "sn35.13:1.14"
msgid "yaṃ ghānaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "nose … "

msgctxt "sn35.13:1.15"
msgid "yaṃ jivhaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, ayaṃ jivhāya assādo. "
msgstr "tongue … "

#. VAR: Yaṃ → yā (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn35.13:1.16"
msgid "Yaṃ jivhā aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā, ayaṃ jivhāya ādīnavo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.13:1.17"
msgid "Yo jivhāya chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ, idaṃ jivhāya nissaraṇaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.13:1.18"
msgid "Yaṃ kāyaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "body … "

msgctxt "sn35.13:1.19"
msgid "yaṃ manaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, ayaṃ manassa assādo. "
msgstr "mind: this is its gratification. "

#. VAR: Yaṃ → yo (bj, s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.13:1.20"
msgid "Yaṃ mano anicco dukkho vipariṇāmadhammo, ayaṃ manassa ādīnavo. "
msgstr "That the mind is impermanent, suffering, and perishable: this is its drawback. "

msgctxt "sn35.13:1.21"
msgid "Yo manasmiṃ chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ, idaṃ manassa nissaraṇan’ti. "
msgstr "Removing and giving up desire and greed for the mind: this is its escape.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.8, sc2
#. VAR: ti → sabbatthāpi evameva itisaddena saha
msgctxt "sn35.13:2.1"
msgid "Yāvakīvañcāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ channaṃ ajjhattikānaṃ āyatanānaṃ evaṃ assādañca assādato, ādīnavañca ādīnavato, nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ nābbhaññāsiṃ, neva tāvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya ‘anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddho’ti paccaññāsiṃ. "
msgstr "As long as I didn’t truly understand these six interior sense fields’ gratification, drawback, and escape in this way for what they are, I didn’t announce my supreme perfect awakening in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.13:2.2"
msgid "Yato ca khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ channaṃ ajjhattikānaṃ āyatanānaṃ evaṃ assādañca assādato, ādīnavañca ādīnavato, nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, athāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya ‘anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddho’ti paccaññāsiṃ. "
msgstr "But when I did truly understand these six interior sense fields’ gratification, drawback, and escape in this way for what they are, I announced my supreme perfect awakening in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.13:2.3"
msgid "Ñāṇañca pana me dassanaṃ udapādi: "
msgstr "Knowledge and vision arose in me: "

#. VAR: vimutti → cetovimutti (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.13:2.4"
msgid "‘akuppā me vimutti, ayamantimā jāti, natthi dāni punabbhavo’”ti. "
msgstr "‘My freedom is unshakable; this is my last rebirth; now there are no more future lives.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.13:2.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

